article_title: White House, GOP Vie to Entice Voters
article_text:
As the spotlight shifts from policy makers in Washington to the presidential campaign trail, the White House and congressional Republicans are looking for ways to energize their parties’ voters—and perhaps attract some from the other side.

On Wednesday, the House passed legislation to repeal central pillars of the 2010 health law and halt federal funding for Planned Parenthood Federation of America. A day earlier, President Barack...
